00:02:58.620 --> 00:03:00.820
So for patients that were eligible for the study,

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:06.380
after screening, they underwent leukophoresis for the manufacturing of the lysosol.

00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:11.540
And after the CAR-T product was finished manufacturing,

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:15.000
they were able to undergo the depletion with Flucide.

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:18.880
Notably, patients were allowed to undergo bridging

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:22.840
while the CAR-T product was being manufactured.

00:03:23.580 --> 00:03:28.600
And approximately 76% of patients in the study did undergo some form of bridging.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:33.140
After lymphodepletion, patients would undergo lysosol infusion,

00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:37.640
and then they would undergo disease assessment on day 30 and onward.

00:03:39.040 --> 00:03:43.500
Based on the initial data, dose level 2 of 100 million CAR-T cells was selected.

00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:48.500
And that's the majority of the patients that you see reported in the TRANSCEND study.

00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:54.560
I include down there the primary endpoints, which was the primary endpoint was a complete remission.

00:03:55.260 --> 00:03:58.300
And key secondary endpoints, this is not exhaustive,

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:02.640
but it included oral response rates, undetectable MRD status,

00:04:03.060 --> 00:04:04.560
PFS, and overall survival.

00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:08.840
This also just summarizes what I just said.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:15.120
And here is, this was later presented in the Lancet by Siddiqui et al. in 2023.

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:18.840
This, the graph on the right shows the patient population,

00:04:18.840 --> 00:04:20.080
but it's summarized there on the left.

00:04:20.900 --> 00:04:25.340
So even though they had approximately 178 patients that were eligible for the study,

00:04:25.340 --> 00:04:28.040
after some patients had to like drop out,

00:04:28.040 --> 00:04:32.480
because they were found to be ineligible prior to lymphodepletion,

00:04:32.720 --> 00:04:35.660
the total number of treated patients was 117.

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:38.440
The median age for this population was 65.

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.120
The median prior lines were five,

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:42.380
including chemo and immunotherapy,

00:04:42.380 --> 00:04:46.880
BTK inhibitor exposure and BCL2 inhibitor treatment.

00:04:47.780 --> 00:04:50.080
So pretty, pretty heavily pretreated population.

00:04:50.420 --> 00:04:51.940
And as I mentioned before,

00:04:51.940 --> 00:04:55.160
high risk cytogenetics were present in approximately 83% of patients.

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:56.560
So a pretty high risk population.

00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:02.180
Of note, also patients had, approximately 44% of patients had bulky disease.

00:05:04.260 --> 00:05:07.860
Given the fact that a BTK inhibitor exposure was one of the inclusion criteria,

00:05:07.860 --> 00:05:10.700
it's not surprising that 100% of them were previously exposed.

00:05:10.700 --> 00:05:15.640
But for the previous venetoclax exposure population, that was approximately 76%.

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:23.800
Here I share some of the efficacy results, again, also presented back in 2023.

00:05:23.800 --> 00:05:26.700
So the complete remission rate was approximately 18%.

00:05:26.700 --> 00:05:27.200
And,

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:31.780
what's notable about that population is that as you can see here in the graph,

00:05:31.780 --> 00:05:34.660
the duration of response, it's the top green curve.

00:05:35.320 --> 00:05:37.060
Those patients actually did surprisingly well.

00:05:37.060 --> 00:05:38.800
They, you know, they didn't achieve,

00:05:40.460 --> 00:05:41.600
or rather they,

00:05:41.960 --> 00:05:44.480
they had a durable benefit to treatment.

00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:46.940
And that was also present in the,

00:05:46.940 --> 00:05:48.180
in the PFS curve.

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.520
So from the secondary outcomes,

00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:53.360
overall response rate was 43%.

00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:56.980
Undetectable MRD status was 63 in the blood and 15.

00:05:56.980 --> 00:05:58.220
59% in the bone marrow.

00:05:58.220 --> 00:06:05.380
And one of the key insights is that undetectable MRD status was associated with an improved PFS,

00:06:05.380 --> 00:06:06.540
but I don't show that curve here.

00:06:06.540 --> 00:06:14.340
The adverse events, primarily, most of the toxicity was hematologic.

00:06:14.340 --> 00:06:20.640
So grade three toxicity was notable for neutropenia, anemia, and thrombocytopenia being common.

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:25.980
CRS was very common in any grade, but severe CRS was only present in approximately 9%.

00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:37.420
And for ICANs like neurotoxicity similarly while it was common severe toxicity was only 18% of node infections were common or at 17%.

00:06:37.420 --> 00:06:41.420
And some of these actually contributed to the mortality rate seen in the study.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:43.920
But overall, the toxicity profile was pretty manageable.

00:06:45.920 --> 00:06:47.840
I don't include the full results here,

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:54.320
but one of the cohorts in the transcend study included adding on the Brutinib in order to see whether or not you could achieve a deeper remission.

00:06:54.320 --> 00:06:55.760
And you can see here that,

00:06:55.760 --> 00:07:01.960
the complete response was much higher at 45% and the overall response rate was 86%.

00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:06.540
So there was some rationale potentially for adding this on and improving responses.

00:07:06.540 --> 00:07:12.080
I wanted to just finish up by including some real-world data that was recently presented at ASH 2025,

00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:20.900
which essentially in this retrospective study showed that in a population of 30 patients across different sites,

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:25.540
that the best CR rate was much higher than was reported in transcend.

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:29.600
At 60% and the best overall response rate was 83%.

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:33.940
Notably, this population was enriched for patients exposed to protobrutinib.

00:07:33.940 --> 00:07:37.320
So this may be potentially reflecting more like real-world practice data.

00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:40.260
So just to conclude,

00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:42.980
the transcend data is still maturing.

00:07:42.980 --> 00:07:45.980
Overall survival data is still also maturing.

00:07:45.980 --> 00:07:49.600
It has Lysosol has received contingent FDA approval.

00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:53.540
So we're looking to see the data as it matures.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:55.320
And one other,

00:07:55.320 --> 00:08:03.240
kind of hypothetical concern in improving CAR-T outcomes in CLL is that we know that CLL T cells are typically dysfunctional.

00:08:03.240 --> 00:08:04.700
But the addition of targeted therapies,

00:08:04.700 --> 00:08:08.100
including BTK inhibitors seems to be promising.

00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:14.140
So this remains potentially an option for patients that are refractory to BTK inhibitors and BCL2 inhibitors.

00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:17.060
All right. Thank you.
